"""Embedded `tools/bazel` wrapper script and its `tools/bazel.md` doc.

These are the base64 of `tools/bazel` (with the five Bazel-derived flag arrays
and the version lines turned into `{{...}}` placeholders) and `tools/bazel.md`
verbatim. Stored base64 to avoid AXL string-literal escaping issues — a raw
string drops the backslash from `\"`, corrupting the wrapper's `array_push`
helper. Regenerable from `tools/bazel` / `tools/bazel.md`.

WRAPPER_TEMPLATE is filled at install time by lib/wrapper.axl; WRAPPER_DOC is
the companion doc.

Regeneration recipe (after editing `tools/bazel` or `tools/bazel.md`):
  1. Build the template text from the EDITED `tools/bazel`:
     - Replace each of the five flag-array bodies (the indented lines between
       `NAME=(` and `)`) with its placeholder line: BAZEL_VERBS -> {{BAZEL_VERBS}},
       BAZEL_VALUE_FLAGS -> {{BAZEL_VALUE_FLAGS}}, BAZEL_BOOL_FLAGS ->
       {{BAZEL_BOOL_FLAGS}}, BAZEL_SHORT_VALUE_FLAGS -> {{BAZEL_SHORT_VALUE_FLAGS}},
       BAZEL_SHORT_BOOL_FLAGS -> {{BAZEL_SHORT_BOOL_FLAGS}}.
     - Replace `ASPECT_BAZEL_WRAPPER_VERSION="..."` -> {{ASPECT_CLI_VERSION}} and
       `ASPECT_BAZEL_WRAPPER_BAZEL_VERSION="..."` -> {{BAZEL_VERSION}} (values only).
     - Assert the text still contains  eval "$1+=(\"\$2\")"  (backslashes intact).
  2. `_WRAPPER_TEMPLATE_B64` = base64 (standard, single line) of that template:
       python3 -c 'import base64,sys;print(base64.standard_b64encode(open(sys.argv[1],"rb").read()).decode())' template.txt
  3. `_WRAPPER_DOC_B64` = base64 of the EDITED `tools/bazel.md` verbatim:
       python3 -c 'import base64,sys;print(base64.standard_b64encode(open(sys.argv[1],"rb").read()).decode())' tools/bazel.md
  4. Replace ONLY the two `_..._B64 = "..."` lines below; leave the rest intact.
"""

load("@std//base64.axl", "base64")

_WRAPPER_TEMPLATE_B64 = ""
_WRAPPER_DOC_B64 = ""

WRAPPER_TEMPLATE = str(base64.decode(_WRAPPER_TEMPLATE_B64))
WRAPPER_DOC = str(base64.decode(_WRAPPER_DOC_B64))
